<h3 align=center>Ignore List</h3>
<p>Ignoring a user will suppress all chat from that user in the Sierra Online lobbies.  You may
both <i>Ignore</i> or <i>Block</i> users, which are <a href="Chat.html#_RefCommands">chat commands</a> that target a user.
They can be accessed via all the normal methods for user based commands.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p><i>Ignore</i> affects only the user name; <i> block</i> disregards all user
names associated with an installation of the game. <i>  Block</i> potentially ignores users you have
never met (if a game is being shared), so be very sure you wish to block someone before doing so.</p>

<p> Users who are ignored or blocked have an appropriate <a href="Icons.html">Icon</a> displayed
next to their name in all <a href="Chat.html#_RefUserList">User Lists</a>.

<p>You can display the contents of your ignore list using the <i>Ignore</i> chat command without
specifying a user.  The <i>Block</i> list can not be displayed, so again, be very sure you wish to block
a user before doing so.</p>

